						<summary>

						<p>On a slab built into the floor in front of the second <hi rend="italic">gōpura</hi> in the Vēdāraṇyēśvara temple.</p>						

						<p>Tuḷajā-mahārāja.</p>						

						<p>This inscription in Marāṭhī language and Nāgarī script of the seventeenth century, records the obeisance of Aṇājā-Rāv-sēṭ and Bhagavant-Rāv-sēṭ, the ministers of the king Tuḷajā-mahārāja. </p>						

						</summary>
